		<p class="large-text center-text" style="margin: 0px;">
			Summary
		</p>
		
		<div class="center-text" style="margin: 20px">
			<p>
				Ray tracing in graphics is a technique that allows the computer to draw extremely real pictures by using physics!
				<br/>
				<br/>
				The idea is that the sun's light hits an object and reflects off that object. What we see are the photons hitting our eyes.
				<br/>
				<img alt="We see a red box when the sunlight reflects off of the box" title="Sunlight reflecting off of a red box" src="weareseeingcolors.png"/>
				<br/>
				We use this concept to generate realistic computer graphics by simulating sunlight reflecting off of three dimensional objects and entering an eye.
				This will allow the computer to simulate shadows, depth, and other interesting things about the object.
			</p>
		</div>
		
